<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-17T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-17T02:00:00-05:00" n="141" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 U.S.S.R./101: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-17T10:00:00+03:00">August 17,
                                    1934—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 17—6:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>256. My 239, August 3, 2 p.m. French Chargé d’Affaires privately states
                            that he has been notified by his Government that there is absolutely no
                            foundation to current and persistent reports that France contemplates a
                            large loan to Russia and credits for the purchase of military material.
                            He also insists that there is no project under consideration for the
                            guaranteeing of commercial credits.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>